  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is correct. It's given that the sum of a number <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"7\"><mn>7</mn></math> is twice as large as a number <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi></math>. This can be described by the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x plus 7 equals 2 y\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></math>. It&rsquo;s also given that the number <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3\"><mn>3</mn></math> less than the number <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math>. This can be described by the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals x minus 3\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>. Therefore, the system consisting of the equations <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x plus 7 equals 2 y\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals x minus 3\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math> describes this situation.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is incorrect. The equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals 3 minus x\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></math> describes a situation where the number <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> less than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3\"><mn>3</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C i